</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F61FFF6FF26F966FC0AF887" blockId="84.[151,1437,1076,2038]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">
Habitat. Infralittoral to circalittoral species, known from 
<quantity id="2E379B383F61FFF6FCAAF966FC41F91A" box="[843,929,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.8" metricValueMax="4.8" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" unit="m" value="28.0" valueMax="48.0" valueMin="8.0">8–48 m</quantity>
depth, most often on coralligenous beds and concretion, possibly on scree made of boulders, sometimes on deep rocks, on detritic coarse sand or in caves; may swim a few centimeters from the substrate (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F61FFF6FD60F8AEFC67F8A3" author="Zander, C. D. &amp; Jelinek, H." box="[641,903,1832,1858]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" pagination="265 - 280" refId="ref66201" refString="Zander, C. D. &amp; Jelinek, H. (1976) Zur demersen Fischfauna im Bereich der Grotte von Banjole (Rovinj / YU) mit Beschreibung von Speleogobius trigloides n. gen. n. sp. (Gobiidae, Perciformes). Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut, 73, 265 - 280." type="journal article" year="1976">Zander &amp; Jelinek 1976</bibRefCitation>
; Miller 1986; Le Bris 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F61FFF6FB60F8AFFB53F8A3" box="[1153,1203,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="84" pageNumber="85">et al</emphasis>
. 2015; 
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F61FFF6FAE9F8AEFA77F8A2" author="Louisy, P." box="[1288,1431,1832,1859]" pageId="84" pageNumber="85" refId="ref60639" refString="Louisy, P. (2015) Europe and Mediterranean Marine Fish Identification Guide. 3 rd Edition. Eugen Ulmer Ed., Paris, 512 pp." type="book" year="2015">Louisy 2015</bibRefCitation>
; Engin 
